metadata.name: Botanical Ghosts #171
metadata.description:
This is a work about growth, impermanence and decay. Ghostly plants and flowers grow around an invisible point, but they immediately begin to fade into the dark background and are soon replaced and covered by others. This process of accumulation and disappearance builds an ever-changing floral garland, or perhaps a funeral wreath.

The monochrome vegetation is part of a fictional flora, born out of random algorithmic combinations, and does not intend to reproduce any real species. It belongs to an “artificial nature” which, like so many worlds that the computers generate for us in movies, games, and virtual reality environments, is a convincing simulation of life, but it is not actually living. AI bots, virtual assistants and non-player characters are also representatives of the uncanny realm of the not-really-alive-but-looking-like-it, which are becoming an increasingly relevant presence in our everyday lives.

These plants and flowers speak about life as a process of incessant renovation, but also about death as the background that’s always there and makes life possible. This spectral vegetation seems to thrive precisely at the verge between both worlds.
_______________


This work is animated and will adapt to any screen size. It generates a never-ending ring of algorithmic foliage, which never repeats itself, and is different for each token. The image preview is triggered after the first five plants or flowers.
Made with p5.js

Controls:
[SPACE] to play/pause
[f] to toggle fullscreen
[s] to download capture

metadata.name: Specter of Fears #41
metadata.description:
In the dreamlike landscape of our minds, the specter of fears is like a wraith, ever-present and ethereal. It whispers in our ear, reminding us of all the things we dare not face. It is a shadow that falls across our hearts, casting a pall of doubt and uncertainty. But even as it haunts us, we must remember that it is a part of us. We must learn to accept its presence, and to use it to our advantage. For fear is not always a curse, it is a guide that shows us where we must grow stronger. It is a companion that walks with us through the dark night, illuminating the path ahead. By embracing our fears, we find the courage to face them, and to overcome them. We find the strength to live fully, to love fiercely, and to pursue our dreams with abandon.

Controls :

• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

Specter of Fears by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2023
Made with Unity
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Shapes of the civilization #89
metadata.description:
In my first generative work, I put together two things about myself: my past and my present/future.
I combine my past as a construction worker, with more than a decade of experience, with my current present of 5 years, as a multimedia artist.

It took me a long time to build this project, there were countless restarts until I finally found the path I wanted to follow.
As a multimedia artist I always like to learn new techniques, and when I discovered fxhash I had no doubts, I wanted to learn creative coding, and this is the result of my work and dedication.

I used elements of architecture mixed with my greatest passion (and also where I spent most of my time until I delve into programming), oil painting!
The color palettes were inspired by some painters I admire, making this work even more special and personal.

In live mode: Press 's' to save as PNG (4800x4800)

Made with p5js and love.
May-June 2022

NFT License 2.0

metadata.name: CMYK:Unchecked #18
metadata.description:
CMYK:Unchecked offers almost infinite canvases designed to challenge the concept and state of being unverified.

Layout variations include 80 / 40 / 20 / 10 / 5 / 4 / 1 circles. 
Each circle presented is either Cyan, Magento, Yellow or Black.

---

This work is of course a parody of 'Checks' by Jack Butcher presented in a transformative way. The work is in no way related to the original 'Checks' work and is not intended to fool anyone into thinking so thus does not affect the originals market or value.

metadata.name: Flume #488
metadata.description:
Flume are infinitely flowing digital bodies of water.
The flow of Flumes can range from slow and gentle, creating small ripples and eddies, to fast and turbulent, carving its way through the inner workings of your computer screen. 
The color, clarity, and viscosity of the water can also vary.

This is the culmination of my collection Flume, an exploration into On-Chain art on Ethereum, https://etherscan.io/address/0x1fa23513825f952afca07a603ac3f312ebee4ca9

These pieces were all created in p5js.

- Andrew

metadata.name: Badgirs City #222
metadata.description:
"I used to live in a small city placed at the center of Iran's plateau with the warmest summer days in the country part; spending most of my childhood with my sweet grandma at her old house. She was always keeping her eyes on me not to get heat stroke at noon playing in the yard when the sun was at its peak glowing furiously. Sundays at noon were my favorite, I used to call them “Ice cream” noons sitting beside the nicest person you could imagine and enjoying a delightful ice cream. You won't know how lovely it was to have an ice cream relaxing under the most enjoyable cold breeze of the tallest windcatcher in the city at her house. "



The Badgirs city is the first collaboration between Fleep and IceRain on Fxhash. The concept was established first with the design of a school with a feeling of safe and nostalgia reminding us of the good memories of our childhood as the grandma’s house and the windcatcher for Fleep.
A windcatcher (Badgir) is an Iranian traditional architectural element in the form of a small tower built on the roof of houses in warm locations to create passive cooling. The collection of Badgirs city is a modern recreational development of those traditional windcatchers designed by Fleep and icerain and exquisitely translated into code by Icerain.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution

metadata.name: RAUSCH #222
metadata.description:
RAUSCH is a series of generative artworks that explore imaginary digital architectures. 

This series challenges traditional notions of architectural representation and raises important questions about the role of resolution in design. Just as the pixel resolution of an image affects its perceived quality, the resolution of an architectural space can affect its qualities and livability. By embracing digital variation through codes, this series explores the interplay between abstract and concrete space through multiple resolutions. 

RAUSCH is inspired by the feeling of being overwhelmed by complex, chaotic and messy sensations, and aims to engage the viewer through a sense of wonder, disorientation, and awe.

Released on the occasion of Companions of Code, a group exhibition by VerticalCrypto Art at The NFT Gallery in London. 
Curated by Micol Ap. Exhibition 10-24 February 2023 

___________________________________________________
RAUSCH Controls:

Animation: 
• ‘1 - 2 - 3 - 4’ animate views
• 'MouseClick' pause/play animation

Functions:
(press key & wait)
• 'F' 24 FPS
• 'B' b/w mode 

Resize Canvas:
(press key & wait)
• '6' Portrait A4 - 1000x1414
• '7' Landscape 16:9 - 1920x1080
• '8' Portrait 9:16 - 1080x1920
• '9' Square 1:1 - 1024x1024
• 'DoubleClick' Fullscreen

Save & Export Image:
• 'S' save a .png of in current resolution

Save & Export GIF:
• 'G' save a 1-2 sec. seamless loop .gif of current view 
• 'P' save a 12-24 sec. seamless loop .gif of all the views
• 'T’ scale down current resolution, save a 12 sec. seamless loop .gif

Steps to save a gif/png :
• go in live/open mode (wait)
• resize canvas with 6,7,8, or 9 to your desired aspect ratio (wait)
• press S,G or P to save & download (wait) 
• enjoy RAUSCH :)

Save & Export GIF for social media sharing:
• go in live/open mode (wait)
• press T or G wait for recalculation & download. 
• enjoy RAUSCH 
• post on Twitter ;)
__________________________________________________

This token may not work on mobile(!), but it allows exporting .png and .gif (see controls) to enjoy RAUSCH on different displays or mobile. Tested on Mozilla, Chrome, Safari. Created with P5js & p5.createLoop

RAUSCH Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2023

metadata.name: Love Note #28
metadata.description:
A love note has no specific form. It can be lengthy, elaborate and composed on scented stationery, or a few poignant words penciled on a scrap of paper or piece of bark. What is communicated and how determine whether it is one or not. 

The range of emotions expressed can span adulation to obsession, and include devotion, disappointment, grief and indignation, self-confidence, ambition, impatience, self-reproach and resignation. 

---------------------------------------------------------------

The collection is inspired by Bauhaus style and gives us an entirely new form of love note. It holds no words so only different composition of shapes and colors let us make interpretations of the emotion each love note express.

It consists of 10 different color palettes and the algorithm ensures that colors would not be mixed between different palettes so that there would be no ambiguity in the message love note is sending. The composition of shapes in each piece is both similar and unique. It can remind us of a paper note pined on a board or an envelope sealed with a stamp. Sandy texture gives each love note warmth and brings it to life.

---------------------------------------------------------------

Color palettes:
-	Pink & Green
-	Water and Sand
-	Ocean Blue
-	Forest Green
-	Very Peri
-	80’s Vibe
-	Ecstatic
-	Warm Mediterranean
-	Dark Blue & Orange
-	Black & Red

---------------------------------------------------------------

Press [s] to download the piece as a png file.

---------------------------------------------------------------

Made in p5js
Created Jan 2023
Artist: Jidoari

metadata.name: Learning to Fly #91

It all started with @chilltulpa saying in fxhash discord "I wish i could make art" and @mknol answering with a few lines of code to create generative art... It was more than enough for me to finally dive in, and try to make something. 

Learning is the key here, learning is being alive.
This is me learning, this is a beginning, I'm learning to fly.
